{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"compacted_at":1784252684965343002,"compiled_state":{"alias":"eastbound-bald-raptors","assignee":"joe-oakhart","attestations":{"plan-review":{"algorithm":"sshsig","author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","envelope":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.opcert.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","head_sha":"ba2fb1dd4fd2cfb3c464cecbb17b66854f446a8b","key_id":null,"kind":"plan-review","manifest":["plan-review: PASS","ticket: 1d75-89cb-f37e-482e","material: 9c6bcfcf30d3156f","model: claude-sonnet-4-6","runner: pydantic_ai","blocking: 0","advisory: 1","rebar-version: 0.7.1 (ba2fb1dd4)","regver: b293b9a55de591cc","verified-at-sha:ba2fb1dd4fd2cfb3c464cecbb17b66854f446a8b","dep absent AGENTS.md"],"material_fingerprint":"9c6bcfcf30d3156f","merged_log_commit":"ba2fb1dd4fd2cfb3c464cecbb17b66854f446a8b","principal":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","signature":null,"signed_at":1784233657901698000}},"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","authorship":{"signed":2,"unsigned":4},"authorship_ledger":[{"content_hash":"ed533f6517e85f16ae1d73778dbf93ecb044e3c95eab3968bcb1b4c2f1040f70","event_uuid":"52e846ff-6d30-4611-b3ec-2f47b7eacd27","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784252684732062001-52e846ff-6d30-4611-b3ec-2f47b7eacd27"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"3b59698ceb62762fd13ee9b74c141fbc76a6f98922f3cf9d7d51aba6499c535f","event_uuid":"1f2c67c0-8f67-47c0-ac14-b186a3f3fd01","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784252684965343001-1f2c67c0-8f67-47c0-ac14-b186a3f3fd01"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-212_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"aa9cb5ff-3fdb-44d3-8af8-c125c27f20ad","comments":[],"created_at":1784230948419240001,"deps":[],"description":"# Spike: verify Claude Code loads AGENTS.md via a `@AGENTS.md` import\n\n## What\n\nDe-risk the whole migration by confirming, hands-on, that a `CLAUDE.md` whose body is a\nsingle `@AGENTS.md` line actually pulls `AGENTS.md` into Claude Code's context at launch\n(the mechanism the research identified, but whose live doc page had a fetch bug). Document\nthe observed precedence/nesting behavior. If the import does NOT work in the installed Claude\nCode version, record the fallback decision (symlink `CLAUDE.md -> AGENTS.md`, accepting its\nWindows/tool-clobber tradeoffs) so downstream stories build on a proven mechanism.\n\n## Scope\n\nA throwaway spike in a scratch dir or worktree — no durable code change. Files touched:\na temporary `AGENTS.md` + `CLAUDE.md`. Output is a written finding recorded as a comment on\nthis ticket (and, if needed, a correction to the approach in the parent epic).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Confirmed whether `@AGENTS.md` in `CLAUDE.md` loads `AGENTS.md` into context in the\n  installed Claude Code build; result recorded as a comment on this ticket with the exact\n  version tested.\n  - Proving: comment on this ticket stating PASS/FAIL + `claude --version`.\n- [ ] If FAIL, the fallback mechanism (symlink vs. content-copy-with-sync-test) is chosen and\n  noted so the AGENTS.md story uses it.\n- [ ] No stray spike files left in the repo working tree.\n  - Proving: `git status --porcelain` clean after the spike.\n\n## De-risking results — SPIKE EXECUTED (PASS, definitive)\n\nRan headless Claude Code **v2.1.211** in an isolated temp dir: `CLAUDE.md` = `@AGENTS.md`,\n`AGENTS.md` held a canary token. The model returned the canary **verbatim** and with **no\napproval prompt** → a project-level `@AGENTS.md` import expands into context. Official docs\n(`code.claude.com/docs/en/memory`) confirm and recommend exactly this: \"Claude Code reads\nCLAUDE.md, not AGENTS.md … create CLAUDE.md [that] imports [it] … add Claude-specific\ninstructions below the import\" (literal example: `@AGENTS.md` then `## Claude Code`). Import\nrecursion max depth = 4 hops; same-repo imports need no approval (only imports OUTSIDE the\nproject tree prompt once). **Decision: use the `@AGENTS.md` import — no symlink fallback needed.**\nKEY NUANCE: imports \"load at launch\" and do NOT reduce context, so AGENTS.md must itself be\nlean; the token win comes from de-dup into docs (drives S2). This spike is resolved;\nimplementation is a no-op adopt-the-proven-pattern.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"AGENTS.md","reason":"throwaway spike verifying @import loads this file"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["parent","81e2-ad5e-bfe2-4653"]],"parent_id":"81e2-ad5e-bfe2-4653","parent_status_uuid":"52e846ff-6d30-4611-b3ec-2f47b7eacd27","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"1d75-89cb-f37e-482e","ticket_type":"task","title":"Spike: verify Claude Code loads AGENTS.md via a `@AGENTS.md` import","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["221d2371-7271-401a-949c-4fc6a6ba699b","da1cfbc5-95ef-41b2-bb99-dd2208a6c2fc","f1d2c166-ba31-4553-ae42-ee0884b32770","9fd75a1b-ad38-4d00-b8bc-c24947138500","52e846ff-6d30-4611-b3ec-2f47b7eacd27","1f2c67c0-8f67-47c0-ac14-b186a3f3fd01"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784252684965343002,"uuid":"0e50c6a1-7667-413a-8d55-a0a219c0c25c"}